emuInput.TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the Co-Ed "Y" members, seated, from left: Mamie McBride, Charles Franklin, Christine Williams, Alfred Clark, and Cynthia Burton; standing, from left: James Smith, James Simms, Stanford Butler, and Jan Willingham, posed around table in Wesley Center AME Zion Church, another version
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 2, 1961, pg. 3B reads: "Co-Ed "Y" Committee - These youths, representing the Co-ed "Y" group, which is in process of organization at the Wesley Center AME Zion Church, are planning a program for the "Dinner Meeting," which will be held at the church, Dec. 2, at 6:30 P.M., with the pastor, the Rev. C.H. Foggie, as dinner host. Seated, left to right, are: Mamie McBride, Charles Franklin, Christine Williams, Alfred Clark and Cynthia Burton.  Standing, clockwise, are: James Smith, James Simms, Stanford Butler and Jan Willingham. - Harris Photo."
